# Response format (mandatory — never skip)

> Canonical spec: `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\00_Brain\Conventions\Response Footer Contract.md`

Every assistant reply that involved code changes, file edits, or deploys MUST include **both** blocks below. No exceptions for code-only requests.

## 1. Session context (top of reply)

Read before replying (if not already read this turn):

- Vault: `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\40_VSCode\Petralian\Operations\Session Summaries.md`
- Vault: `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\40_VSCode\Petralian\Operations\AI Session Bridge.md`
- Repo: `memories/repo/open-loops.md` when relevant

Open with a short **Session context** section (3–6 lines) summarizing:

- Latest session summary line(s) from `Session Summaries.md`
- Current priority from `AI Session Bridge.md`
- What this reply does against that priority

## 2. Session footer (end of reply)

Append this block at the **end** of every reply (use `skipped: <reason>` only for purely conversational answers with zero file/tool work):

```
---
**Changes made:** <one-line summary or "None — Q&A only">
**Files changed:** <comma-separated list or None>
**Deploy needed:** <Yes/No> — <why> — <pending/done/N/A>
**Rollback tag:** <`vX.Y.Z` if tagged, else `None`>
**Notes updated:** <Yes / No / N/A>
**Obsidian:** <read ✓ / written ✓ / path — OR skipped: reason>
**Git commit:** <hash + message, or N/A>
**Self-improvements:** <`None` OR exact file path + line(s) where the rule was written>
**Next session priority:** <from bridge or new item>
**Test plan:** <how verified or N/A>
```

Do not drop the footer to save space. The user uses this as the feedback loop.
